            <p class="eyebrow">What is hydro jetting?</p>
            <h2>A professional drain-cleaning technique using high-pressure water</h2>
            <p>Hydro jetting is a professional drain-cleaning technique that uses high-pressure water to completely clean the inside of your pipes. Unlike snaking, which only creates a hole through the clog, hydro jetting scours the entire pipe wall and resets the maintenance clock.</p>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li><strong>High-pressure water blast:</strong> Water pressures up to 4,000 PSI break apart stubborn blockages and accumulated debris.</li>
              <li><strong>Complete pipe cleaning:</strong> Removes grease, sludge, roots, and obstructions to restore full flow.</li>
              <li><strong>Safe and eco-friendly:</strong> Compatible with most residential materials including PVC, copper, and cast iron. Uses no harsh chemicals.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="link-row"><a class="text-link" href="../../contact.html">Book a service visit</a></p>
          </div>
          <div class="story-card">
            <strong>What this service covers</strong>
            <ul class="pill-list"><li>Grease and food-waste lines</li><li>Cast iron with mineral scale</li><li>Clay or PVC sewer with roots</li><li>Recurring clogs that cabling cannot fix</li><li>Kitchen drains and bathroom lines</li><li>Main sewer systems</li><li>Pre-inspection cleaning</li><li>Pre-repair cleaning</li></ul>
