            <p class="eyebrow">FAQs</p>
            <h2>Hydro jetting FAQs</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="trust-stack">
            <article><span>Q</span><div><h3>Is hydro jetting safe for all pipes?</h3><p>Yes, hydro jetting is safe for most residential materials including PVC, copper, and cast iron. Our technicians adjust pressure based on pipe type and condition to ensure effective cleaning without damage.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>Q</span><div><h3>How often should I have my drains hydro jetted?</h3><p>We recommend hydro jetting every 1 to 2 years as preventative maintenance. Homes with heavy use, older pipes, or recurring clog issues may benefit from more frequent service.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>Q</span><div><h3>Can hydro jetting remove tree roots?</h3><p>Yes, hydro jetting is highly effective at clearing invasive tree roots from sewer lines. For ongoing root problems, we can also recommend root treatments to prevent regrowth.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>Q</span><div><h3>What is the difference between hydro jetting and snaking?</h3><p>Snaking creates a hole through the clog, providing temporary relief. Hydro jetting comprehensively clears the entire pipe interior, removing all buildup from the pipe walls for a thorough, lasting clean.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>Q</span><div><h3>Is hydro jetting environmentally friendly?</h3><p>Yes. Hydro jetting uses only high-pressure water with no harmful chemicals, making it an eco-friendly drain cleaning solution that is safe for your home and the environment.</p></div></article>
